interactions.flavorLineOne: The Iron Lord is wary of Rasputin's motives, and encourages you to return to the Iron Banner and hone your skills in preparation for the coming conflict.
Saladin advises against trusting Osiris, and encourages you to test your newfound strength in the Iron Banner.

Lord Saladin thanks you for your hard work. You've set a strong example for Guardians who wish to follow in the footsteps of the Iron Lords.

He asks that you carry these lessons forward, even after the Iron Banner has ended.

The Red Legion has been laid low. You've done well. Now, the time is right for the Iron Banner to return. Show me you can triumph in battles of Light versus Light, and I will reward you with relics from the Dark Age: the armor and weapons of the Iron Lords.
Fought like a Lord of Iron. You've earned this. This City needs more Guardians like you: purveyors of the old way.
Saladin congratulates you on your performance in the Iron Banner, and offers a reward worthy of such a champion.

Lord Saladin congratulates you on a job well done. You've shown your opponents the importance of being prepared for anything.

"They've seen what it takes to win," he says. "Now show them how to keep winning."
Lord Saladin congratulates you on your efforts in the Iron Banner and offers a reward worthy of such a performance.

headerDisplayProperties.description: Return to Lord Saladin to claim your reward.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Iron Banner: Season 3

interactions.flavorLineOne:
Lord Saladin is pleased: You've demonstrated the spirit of the Iron Banner and taught your opponents the humility of defeat.

“New Guardians can learn something from watching you,” he says. “Now I want you to show them what it means to dominate the arena.”

Lord Saladin is impressed with your ability to take control of a fight. He hopes his new recruits are paying close attention, and he has another lesson for you to teach.

"Some new Guardians are shy about using their Light," he says. "Show them a better way."

"You've shown your opponents what it means to truly wield the Light," Lord Saladin says when you return. "Now make them work harder."

Some new recruits seem too reliant on their favorite weapons. He wants you to show your fellow Guardians that it pays to be well-rounded.
Complete Iron Banner matches to obtain Iron Banner tokens and earn Level 20 rewards from this faction.
Show Lord Saladin proof of your deeds in the Iron Banner.
Your reputation in the Iron Banner precedes you. Take this reward in recognition of your deeds.
